body:
I tried the latest beta, but got errors accessing onedrive

2018/10/03 22:46:17 Unable to get drive_id and drive_type. If you are upgrading from older versions of rclone, please run `rclone config` and re-configure this backend.

after running rclone config I got:

2018/10/03 22:48:26 Failed to query available drives: HTTP error 401 (401 Unauthorized) returned body: "{
  "error": {
    "code": "InvalidAuthenticationToken",
    "message": "CompactToken parsing failed with error code: 8004920A",
    "innerError": {
      "request-id": "xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx",
      "date": "2018-10-03T20:48:26"
    }
  }
}"

So I installed the latest stable version and it worked again, and still got the onenote error (which is to be expected). I did the authorization however with the stable rclone version on a windows desktop and used the beta version on debian. Maybe this is the cause of the above errors or is there a bug?
